<TITLE> HC stays graft case against BNP's Zia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 22 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court has halted for six months the proceedings of a graft case against BNP leader and former state minister Ziaul Haque Zia. A bench of justice Md Dastagir Hossain and justice Md Raisuddin made the order on Thursday. It also issued a rule nisi on the government and the Anti-Corruption Commission to explain within four weeks why the charge framing order in the case should not be cancelled. Advocate TH Khan stood for Zia while deputy attorney general Zahid Sarwar Kajal represented the state. The ACC on Feb 14 filed the case against the former state minister with Ramganj Police Station in Laxmipur for embezzling 320 metric tonnes of rice. Zia petitioned the HC after a trial court on Aug 19 indicted him in the case. Zia fled the country during emergency rule. He returned home on Feb 13 this year and was arrested a few days later. The BNP leader was convicted in a number of cases  he was sentenced to 13 years in a graft case, eight years in a tax dodge case and 10 years in a bribe case. bdn
